---
import PresentationLayout from '~/layouts/PresentationLayout.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Agentic Coding: Prompting & Context Management',
  description: 'How to manage context windows, structure work into sessions, write prompt documents, and use permission modes effectively.',
  ignoreTitleTemplate: false,
};
---

<PresentationLayout metadata={metadata}>
  <!-- Slide 1: Title -->
  <section data-state="title" class="title-slide">
    <h1>Agentic Coding</h1>
    <h2>Prompting & Context Management</h2>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 2: About Me -->
  <section>
    <h2>About Me</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem; max-width: 80%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">🛠️</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">15 years of software engineering experience</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">❤️</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">I genuinely enjoy coding and building software</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">🏗️</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">Currently building <strong>Agewise</strong> as CTO</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.5rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">🤖</span>
        <p style="margin: 0;">Me and my team delegate <strong>99% of coding</strong> to AI agents</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 3: Agenda -->
  <section>
    <h2>Agenda</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Context Window Management</li>
      <li>Session Strategy</li>
      <li>Prompting with Documents</li>
      <li>Permission Modes as Workflow</li>
      <li>Guidelines: Codebase Consistency vs. Rules</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== Section 1: Context Window Management ==================== -->

  <!-- Slide 4: The Context Rot Problem -->
  <section>
    <h2>The Context Rot Problem</h2>
    <p style="color: #a0aec0; margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">More context you have in a session, the worse it gets</p>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.25rem;">
      <div class="content-box red">
        <div class="content-box-content" style="text-align: center;">
          <h3>Attention Degrades</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Agent drifts from instructions, makes unexpected decisions</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box red">
        <div class="content-box-content" style="text-align: center;">
          <h3>Latency Rises</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Each response takes longer as the model processes more tokens</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box red">
        <div class="content-box-content" style="text-align: center;">
          <h3>Cost Growth</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">You hit rate limits and token caps faster</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center;">
        I am skeptical about 1M token models. I code everything within <strong>100–150K tokens</strong> per session.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 5: The 75% Rule -->
  <section>
    <h2>The 75% Rule</h2>
    <div style="margin-top: 2rem; max-width: 85%; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;">
      <!-- Context meter -->
      <div style="display: flex; border-radius: 12px; overflow: hidden; height: 4rem; font-size: 0.95rem; font-weight: 600;">
        <div style="flex: 50; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.25); border: 2px solid #4ade80; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-right: none; border-radius: 12px 0 0 12px;">
          0–50% — High accuracy
        </div>
        <div style="flex: 25; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.25); border: 2px solid #f0c36d; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-right: none;">
          50–75% — Wrap up
        </div>
        <div style="flex: 25; background: rgba(232, 180, 184, 0.25); border: 2px solid #e8b4b8; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; border-radius: 0 12px 12px 0;">
          75%+ — Danger
        </div>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; margin-top: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.85rem; color: #a0aec0;">
        <span>0K</span>
        <span>100K</span>
        <span>150K</span>
        <span>200K</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="margin-top: 2rem;">
      <p style="text-align: center; font-size: 1.1rem; color: #a0aec0;">
        Closer to 75% — do not start new assignments unless they are very small and simple.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1rem;">
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center;">
        <strong>75% of 200K = 150K tokens.</strong> That's your ceiling, not 100%.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 6: Monitor Your Context -->
  <section>
    <h2>Monitor Your Context</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.25rem; margin-top: 2rem;">
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">📊</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>Custom Status Line</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Configure to always see your context %. Run <code style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.2); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.9rem;">/statusline</code> and ask it to show context window usage.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box">
        <span class="content-box-icon">🔍</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3><code style="font-size: 1.3rem;">/context</code> Command</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Run after every few prompts. Know where you stand before sending the next instruction.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="border: 2px solid #f0c36d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.1); margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center;">
        If you don't track it, you can't manage it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 7: Disable Auto-Compact -->
  <section>
    <h2>Disable Auto-Compact</h2>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem;">
      <div class="content-box red">
        <span class="content-box-icon">⚠️</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>The Problem</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">Auto-compact removes information from your context without telling you what was lost. Your instructions, constraints, or decisions may silently disappear. You lose control.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box green">
        <span class="content-box-icon">✅</span>
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>The Fix</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            <code style="background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.2); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 1rem;">"autoCompact": false</code>
            <br />Manage your sessions manually. When context gets high — ask to summarize what was done, review it, and use it as the beginning of the next session.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 8: One Task Per Session -->
  <section>
    <h2>One Task Per Session</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem;">
      <div class="content-box red">
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>One session for everything</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            Table + filters + sorting + adjustments + bug fixes
            <br /><br />
            Context bloats. Agent drifts. Quality drops.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="content-box green">
        <div class="content-box-content">
          <h3>One focused task per session</h3>
          <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
            Session 1: Table with filters
            <br />Session 2: Sorting and Adjustments
            <br />Session 3: Bug fixes from review
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center;">
        When you see the task growing bigger than expected — <strong>stop. Start a new session.</strong>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== Section 2: Session Strategy ==================== -->

  <!-- Slide 9: Section Title -->
  <section>
    <h2 style="font-size: 2.5rem;">Session Strategy</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: #a0aec0; margin-top: 1rem;">Think in Sessions, Not in Prompts</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 10: Two Types of Sessions -->
  <section>
    <h2>Two Types of Sessions</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div style="border: 3px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1);">
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Investigation Sessions</h3>
        <ul style="font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; padding: 0;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">🔍 Explore, analyze, ask questions</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">📖 Read-only mode</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">⚡ Can consume 50%+ context</li>
          <li>📄 Output = understanding + written analysis</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div style="border: 3px solid #4ade80; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.1);">
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Execution Sessions</h3>
        <ul style="font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; padding: 0;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">🛠️ Execute part or entire plan</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">📋 Plan mode → accept edits</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">📉 Context stays low (narrow scope)</li>
          <li>💻 Output = working code</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 11: Session Lifecycle -->
  <section>
    <h2>Session Lifecycle</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr auto 1fr; align-items: center; gap: 0.5rem; margin: 2rem auto; max-width: 95%;">
      <div style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.15); border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; padding: 1rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center;">
        <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; margin: 0 0 0.35rem 0;">Investigate</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0; margin: 0;">Can we implement X? Does this API support Y? How does it affect tests?</p>
      </div>
      <span style="color: #0ea5c1; font-size: 1.5rem;">→</span>
      <div style="background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.15); border: 2px solid #f0c36d; padding: 1rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center;">
        <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; color: #f0c36d; margin: 0 0 0.35rem 0;">Document</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0; margin: 0;">Idea, behaviors, technical details</p>
      </div>
      <span style="color: #0ea5c1; font-size: 1.5rem;">→</span>
      <div style="background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.15); border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; padding: 1rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center;">
        <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; margin: 0 0 0.35rem 0;">Plan</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0; margin: 0;">Give doc to agent. Review plan.</p>
      </div>
      <span style="color: #0ea5c1; font-size: 1.5rem;">→</span>
      <div style="background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.15); border: 2px solid #4ade80; padding: 1rem 0.75rem; border-radius: 10px; text-align: center;">
        <p style="font-size: 0.85rem; font-weight: 700; color: #4ade80; margin: 0 0 0.35rem 0;">Execute</p>
        <p style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #a0aec0; margin: 0;">Implement. One task at a time.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1rem;">
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 1rem;">
        💡 You can also use Claude to help generate the document. Start in read-only, then ask it to write findings into your doc.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div style="border: 2px solid #f0c36d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.1); margin-top: 0.75rem;">
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        If your feature or change is not big or complex — skip investigation and start with <strong>Plan mode</strong> directly.<br />
        For bigger features, I start with Investigation and Document phases.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 12: Feature Document vs. Claude Code Plan -->
  <section>
    <h2>Your Document vs. Agent's Plan</h2>
    <div style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 2rem; margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <div style="border: 3px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1);">
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #0ea5c1;">Your Feature Document</h3>
        <ul style="font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; padding: 0;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">📝 What you're building (idea)</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">🎯 How it should behave (test cases)</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">⚙️ Technical decisions (names, endpoints)</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">🧑 Written by you, at your pace</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="text-align: center; font-weight: 700; color: #0ea5c1; margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 1.1rem;">The WHAT and the HOW</p>
      </div>
      <div style="border: 3px solid #f0c36d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.1);">
        <h3 style="margin-bottom: 1rem; color: #f0c36d;">Agent's Execution Plan</h3>
        <ul style="font-size: 1rem; list-style: none; padding: 0;">
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">📋 Execution steps from your document</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">📁 File-by-file changes</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">🔢 Order of implementation</li>
          <li style="margin-bottom: 0.6rem;">🤖 Generated by agent in plan mode</li>
        </ul>
        <p style="text-align: center; font-weight: 700; color: #f0c36d; margin-top: 1rem; font-size: 1.1rem;">The execution sequence</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1); margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center;">
        You define <strong>what</strong> and <strong>how</strong>. The agent figures out the execution details.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 13: Real Example: LLM Provider Migration -->
  <section>
    <h2>Real Example: LLM Provider Migration</h2>
    <p style="color: #a0aec0; font-size: 1rem; margin-bottom: 1.25rem;">Migrate from direct LLM API calls to OpenRouter across 10 modules</p>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.6rem; max-width: 90%; margin: 0 auto;">
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="background: #0ea5c1; color: #030620; font-weight: 700; padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 0.85rem; flex-shrink: 0;">Session 1</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Investigated all 10 modules. Checked parameter compatibility. <span style="color: #f0c36d;">Consumed 60% of context.</span></p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="background: #f0c36d; color: #030620; font-weight: 700; padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 0.85rem; flex-shrink: 0;">Document</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Offloaded all findings and analysis into a document. Not a plan yet — <span style="color: #f0c36d;">analysis that I need to verify every detail.</span></p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="background: #0ea5c1; color: #030620; font-weight: 700; padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 0.85rem; flex-shrink: 0;">Session 2</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Implemented OpenRouter service based on verified analysis.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="background: #0ea5c1; color: #030620; font-weight: 700; padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 0.85rem; flex-shrink: 0;">Session 3</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Migrated first module. Documented learnings.</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: flex-start; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="background: #4ade80; color: #030620; font-weight: 700; padding: 0.25rem 0.6rem; border-radius: 6px; font-size: 0.85rem; flex-shrink: 0;">Session 4+</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 0.95rem;">Migrated remaining modules using subagents, using the learning from the first migration.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="border: 2px solid #f0c36d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.1); margin-top: 1rem;">
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        In many cases you don't want to start execution in the same session as investigation. Your context is already spent on understanding.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ==================== Section 3: Prompting with Documents ==================== -->

  <!-- Slide 14: Section Title -->
  <section>
    <h2 style="font-size: 2.5rem;">Prompting with Documents</h2>
    <p style="font-size: 1.5rem; color: #a0aec0; margin-top: 1rem;">Stop Typing in the Terminal</p>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 15: The Drip-Feed Problem -->
  <section>
    <h2>The Drip-Feed Problem</h2>
    <div style="border: 2px solid #e8b4b8; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.25rem; background: rgba(232, 180, 184, 0.05); margin-bottom: 1rem;">
      <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; font-size: 0.9rem;">
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem;">
          <span style="color: #0ea5c1; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">You:</span>
          <span>"Create a chat feature. Chat component should open when clicking on chat button. Chat component displays the list of all messages"</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem;">
          <span style="color: #4ade80; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">Agent:</span>
          <span style="color: #a0aec0; font-style: italic;">builds something</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem;">
          <span style="color: #0ea5c1; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">You:</span>
          <span>"Add a spinner after sending a message"</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem;">
          <span style="color: #4ade80; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">Agent:</span>
          <span style="color: #a0aec0; font-style: italic;">adds spinner</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem;">
          <span style="color: #0ea5c1; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">You:</span>
          <span>"Wait, you should use a spinner from components library"</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem;">
          <span style="color: #4ade80; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">Agent:</span>
          <span style="color: #a0aec0; font-style: italic;">refactors</span>
        </div>
        <div style="display: flex; gap: 0.75rem;">
          <span style="color: #0ea5c1; font-weight: 700; flex-shrink: 0;">You:</span>
          <span>"When we open the chat we should always call GET /history endpoints so that user does not start with blank chat"</span>
        </div>
        <div style="text-align: center; color: #a0aec0; margin-top: 0.25rem;">...10 rounds later, 90% context used</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="border: 2px solid #0ea5c1; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(14, 165, 193, 0.1);">
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        If you can't write a longer prompt — you probably don't know what you want yet.<br />
        That's the signal to sit down, think, and describe the idea on paper.
      </p>
    </div>
    <div style="border: 2px solid #f0c36d; border-radius: 12px; padding: 1rem; background: rgba(240, 195, 109, 0.1); margin-top: 0.75rem;">
      <p style="margin: 0; text-align: center; font-size: 0.95rem;">
        <strong>Testing problem:</strong> without the full picture upfront, the agent can't write tests for desired behavior — it tests <em>what it built</em>, not <em>what it should do</em>. With behaviors defined upfront, they become your test cases.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Slide 16: The Document Approach -->
  <section>
    <h2>The Document Approach</h2>
    <div class="content-box green" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
      <span class="content-box-icon">📄</span>
      <div class="content-box-content">
        <h3>Create a feature document in your repo</h3>
        <p style="color: #a0aec0;">
          <code style="background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.2); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.9rem;">prompt.md</code> (gitignored) or
          <code style="background: rgba(74, 222, 128, 0.2); padding: 0.15rem 0.4rem; border-radius: 4px; font-size: 0.9rem;">docs/chat-feature.md</code>
          
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div style="display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; margin-top: 1.25rem;">
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.3rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">✍️</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 1rem;">Write everything you want before starting</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.3rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">☕</span>
        <p style="margin: 0; font-size: 1rem;">Take your time — hours, coffee breaks, next day</p>
      </div>
      <div style="display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem;">
        <span style="font-size: 1.3rem; min-width: 2rem; text-align: center;">👥</span>
